  sectionId (39870)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title [Repealed].
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39870&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of Scheduled Tribes Orders.—(1) Rep. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39871)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Common High Court for Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39871&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be a common High Court for the States of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur,`
  line `Tripura and Mizoram to be called the Gauhati High Court (the High Court of Assam, Nagaland,`
  line `Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram) (hereinafter referred to as the common High Court);`
  line
  line `(b) the Judges of the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura holding`
  line `office immediately before that day shall, unless they have elected otherwise, become on that day the`
  line `Judges of the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenditure in respect of the salaries and allowances of the Judges of the common High`
  line `Court shall be allocated amongst the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland and`
  line `Tripura and the Union in such proportion as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39872)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Provision as to advocates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39872&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in section 3 in sub-section (1), for clause (b), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(b) for the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland and Tripura and the`
  line `Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh, to be known as the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland,`
  line `Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram;"`
  line
  line `(b) the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripua shall be deemed to be`
  line `the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise in`
  line `the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura, shall be entitled to practise as an`
  line `advocate in the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) All persons who, immediately, before the appointed day, are advocates on the roll of the Bar Council`
  line `of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura, shall as from that day, become advocates on the roll`
  line `of the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram.`
  line
  line `(4) The right of audience in the common High Court shall be regulated in accordance with the like`
  line `principles as, immediately before the appointed day, are in force with respect to the right of audience in`
  line `the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura:`
  line
  line `Provided that as among the Advocates-General of the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram,`
  line `Nagaland and Tripura, the right of audience shall be determined with reference to their dates of enrolment as`
  line advocates.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39873)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Practice and procedure in the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39873&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the`
  line `law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court`
  line `of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in`
  line `relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39874)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Custody of seal of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39874&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day with respect to the custody of the Seal of the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and`
  line `Tripura shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the`
  line `common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39875)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39875&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with`
  line `respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Assam,`
  line `Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura shall, with necessary modifications, apply with respect to the`
  line `form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39876)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39876&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Assam, Nagaland,`
  line `Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura and with respect to all matter, ancillary to the exercise of those`
  line `powers shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39877)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Principal seat and other places of sitting of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39877&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The principal seat`
  line `of the common High Court shall be at the same place at which the principal seat of the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura is located immediately before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may, by notified order, provide for the establishment of a permanent bench or benches`
  line `of the common High Court at one or more places within the territories to which the jurisdiction of the High`
  line `Court extends, other than the principal seat of the High Court, and for any matters connected therewith:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any order under this sub-section, the President shall consult the Chief`
  line `Justice of the common High Court and the Governor of the State in which the bench or benches is or are`
  line `proposed to be established.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Judges and division`
  line `courts of the common High Court may also sit at such other place or places in the States of Assam,`
  line `Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram as the Chief Justice may, with the approval of the`
  line `Governor of the State concerned, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39878)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39878&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya,`
  line `Manipur and Tripura and the Judges and division courts thereof shall, with the necessary modifications,`
  line `apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39906)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Transfer of proceedings from the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura to the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39906&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) All proceedings pending in the High Court of Assam,`
  line `Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura immediately before the appointed day shall, from such day,`
  line `stand transferred to the common High Court`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding transferred under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of by the common High Court`
  line `as if such proceeding was entertained by the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39880)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39880&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 23,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review,`
  line `petitions for revision and petitions for writs; and`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division court`
  line `thereof; and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including references`
  line `to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39881)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39881&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura and was authorised to appear or to act in any`
  line `proceedings transferred from the said High Court to the common High Court under section 23 shall have the`
  line `right to appear or to act, as the case may be, in the common High Court in relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39882)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39882&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the common High Court of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be made on`
  line `or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority having`
  line `power to make such provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (39883)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 27
  title `Non-applicability of this Part to the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 12 (date to be notified).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39883&sectionno=26A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Non-applicability of this Part to the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.— On`
  line `and from the date of commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, the provisions of sections 15 to 26 (both inclusive) shall not apply to the`
  line `States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39884)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by the Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39884&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President may,`
  line `at any time before the appointed day, authorise by order such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `State of Mizoram as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the`
  line `appointed day, pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of the State of`
  line `Mizoram:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Mizoram may, after the appointed day, authorise by order such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Mizoram for any period not`
  line `extending beyond the said period of six months.`
  line
  line `(2) The President or, as the case may be, the Governor of Mizoram shall make separate orders`
  line `under sub-section (1) in respect of periods falling in different financial years.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39885)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of the existing Union territory of Mizoram.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39885&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports`
  line `of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in section 49 of the Government of Union`
  line `Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963), relating to the accounts of the existing Union territory of Mizoram in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be submitted to the Governor of Mizoram who shall`
  line `cause them to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may, by order,—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of the existing Union territory of`
  line `Mizoram on any service in respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial`
  line `year 1986-87 or in respect of any earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service`
  line `and for that year as disclosed in the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39886)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Allowances and privileges of Governor of Mizoram.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39886&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and privileges of the`
  line `Governor of Mizoram shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under clause (3) of`
  line `Article 158, be such as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39887)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39887&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The President shall, by order, determine the grants-in-aid of the`
  line `revenues of the State of Mizoram and the share of that State in the Union duties of excise, estate duty and`
  line `taxes on income and for that purpose amend thereby the relevant provisions of the Additional Duties of`
  line `Excise (Goods of Special (Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), the Union Duties of Excise (Distribution)`
  line `Act, 1979 (24 of 1979), the Estate Duty (Distribution) Act, 1962 (9 of 1962) and the Constitution`
  line `(Distribution of Revenues) Order, 1985 in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39888)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Property, assets, rights, liabilities, obligations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39888&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) All such property and assets within the`
  line `existing Union territory of Mizoram as are held immediately before the appointed day by the Union for`
  line `purposes of governance of that Union territory shall, on and from that day, pass to the State of Mizoram`
  line `unless the purposes for which such property and assets are so held are Union purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cash balances in the treasuries in the Union territory of Mizoram before the appointed`
  line `day shall, as from that day, vest in the State of Mizoram.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligations (other than those relatable to, or in connection with, a Union`
  line `purpose), whether arising out of any contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before the appointed`
  line day,—
  line
  line `(a) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Central Government arising out of, or in connection`
  line `with, the governance of the Union territory of Mizoram; or`
  line
  line `(b) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Administrator of the existing Union territory of`
  line `Mizoram in his capacity as such, or of the Government of that Union territory,`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Government of the State`
  line `of Mizoram.`
  line
  line `(3) The right to recover arrears of—`
  line
  line `(a) any tax or duty being a tax or duty enumerated in the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution; or`
  line
  line `(b) any duty referred to in article 268; or`
  line
  line `(c) any tax under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956),`
  line
  line `which have fallen due in the existing Union territory of Mizoram shall pass to the State of Mizoram.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to or in relation to,—`
  line
  line `(a) any institution, undertaking or project the expenditure in relation to which is immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, met from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India;`
  line
  line `(b) any property which has been placed by the Union at the disposal of the administration of the`
  line `existing Union territory of Mizoram subject to the condition that the ownership thereof will continue to`
  line `vest in the Union.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "liability" includes liability in respect of any civil deposit, local fund deposit, charitable`
  line `or other endowment, provident fund account, pension or actionable wrong;`
  line
  line `(b) "Union purposes" means the purposes of Government relatable to any of the matters mentioned`
  line `in the Union List.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39889)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Provision relating to All India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39889&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Indian Administrative Service,`
  line `the Indian Police Service and the Indian Forest Service who, immediately before the appointed day, is`
  line `holding any post in the existing Union territory of Mizoram shall, until otherwise directed by the Central`
  line `Government, be deemed to be on deputation, on and from the appointed day, to the Government of the`
  line `State of Mizoram on the same terms and conditions of service as are applicable to him under the relevant`
  line `cadre rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of such deputation shall in no case extend beyond a period of three years`
  line `from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "cadre rules" means the Indian Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules,`
  line `1954, the Indian Police Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954 or the Indian Forest Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39890)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Provisions relating to other services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39890&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who immediately before the appointed`
  line `day is serving in connection with the affairs of the Union under the administrative control of the`
  line `Administrator of the Union territory of Mizoram shall, unless otherwise directed by an order of the`
  line `Central Government, be deemed to have been allocated for service as from that day in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State of Mizoram:`
  line
  line `Provided that no directions shall be issued under this section after the expiry of a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to persons to whom the provisions of`
  line `section 32 apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39891)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Other provisions as to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39891&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this section or section 33 shall be deemed to`
  line `affect on or after the appointed day the operations of the provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the`
  line `Constitution in relation to determination of the conditions of service of persons serving in connection with`
  line `the affairs of the State of Mizoram:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of`
  line `any person referred to in section 33 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person deemed to have been allocated under`
  line `section 33 in connection with the administration of the Union territory of Mizoram, shall be deemed to`
  line `have been rendered in connection with the affairs of the State of Mizoram for the purposes of the rules`
  line `regulating his conditions of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39892)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39892&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Every person who immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the Union territory of Mizoram shall continue to hold the same post or office and shall be deemed, on`
  line `and from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or other`
  line `appropriate authority in, the State of Mizoram on the same terms and conditions of appointment and on`
  line `the same tenure as he was holding the post or office immediately before that day:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority on or after the`
  line `appointed day from passing in relation to such person any order affecting his continuance in such post or`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39893)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39893&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order, establish one or more Advisory`
  line `Committees for the purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the discharge of its functions under this Part; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `Part and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39894)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Prohibition of representation after certain period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39894&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any law or rule for the time being in force, no representation shall lie against any order`
  line `passed under the provisions of this Part on the expiry of three months from the date of publication or`
  line `service, whichever is earlier, of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, suo motu or otherwise and for reasons to be recorded,`
  line `re-open any matter and pass such orders thereon as may appear to it to be appropriate if it is satisfied that`
  line `it is necessary so to do in order to prevent any miscarriage of justice to any affected person.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39895)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39895&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the Government of the State of Mizoram as may appear to it to be necessary for the purpose`
  line `of giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and the State Government shall comply with such`
  line directions.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
