obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39900)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Continuance of existing laws and their adaptations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39900&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, in the existing Union territory of Mizoram shall continue to be in force in the State of`
  line `Mizoram until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of Mizoram of any law made`
  line `before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, within two years from that day, by order,`
  line `make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be`
  line `necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and`
  line `modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other competent`
  line authority.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means, as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, the Central`
  line `Government, and as respects any other law, the Government of the State of Mizoram.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39901)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39901&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 43 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in`
  line `relation to the State of Mizoram, construe the law in such manner not affecting the substance as may be`
  line `necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39902)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Provisions as to continuance of courts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39902&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `All courts and tribunals and all authorities`
  line `discharging lawful functions throughout the existing Union territory of Mizoram or any part thereof`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall, unless their continuance is inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act or until other provision is made by a competent legislature or other competent authority, continue`
  line `to exercise their respective functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39903)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title `Effect of provisions of Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39903&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39904)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39904&sectionno=47&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39905)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034&sectionId=39905&sectionno=48&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00054_198634_1517807327034
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under the section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and it, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
